						<div class="postbody">Plenty of Game Boy games run at 30 fps so that the slow LCD can keep up. The launch titles were developed on Wide Boy (SGB predecessor), so they show up blurrier on the LCD than the developers had seen on the CRT, but later titles used a lower frame rate to correct for this.
<br />
<br />Films run at 24 fps, but they have natural motion blur to hide things.</div>

